## Reference TX_H4_ref: 4 exons, Comparator TX_H4_comp: 2 exons
## Exon1: 60000-60200 (- strand exon 4), Exon2: 60400-60403 (4bp, - exon 3)
## Exon3: 60600-60601 (2bp, - exon 2), Exon4: 60800-61000 (- exon 1)
## CDS: 60000-61000 (all CDS)
## On - strand: 5'→3' order is exon4(60800-61000), exon3(60600-60601),
##   exon2(60400-60403), exon1(60000-60200)
## SE on exon3 (60600-60601, 2bp): processed FIRST (more 5' on minus)
## SE on exon2 (60400-60403, 4bp): processed SECOND
## Correct order: LOSS 2bp → offset 1, then LOSS 4bp → cumulative -6 → offset 0 (compensated)
## Wrong order (ascending): LOSS 4bp → offset 2, then LOSS 2bp → offset 0 (same outcome here)
## But the frameshift/compensatory FLAGS differ:
## Correct: event at 60600 is frameshift, event at 60400 is compensatory
## Wrong: event at 60400 is frameshift, event at 60600 is compensatory
